<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Leicester have completed the signing of defender Timothy Castagne from Atalanta in a deal worth £22million. </p>

<p>The 24-year-old, who has traditionally played as a right back but can also operate from the left, has penned a five-year deal with the Foxes. </p>

<p>A Belgian international with seven caps, Castagne has been brought in by Brendan Rodgers following the sale of Ben Chilwell to Chelsea last week for £50m. </p>

<p>More to follow...  </p>

<p>Timothy Castagne has penned a five-year deal with Leicester City in a £22million deal</p>
